					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Write a Letter</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-08-19T16:26:15+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">August 19, 2014 12:26 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">August 19, 2014 12:26 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/19/today-in-small-business-write-a-letter/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Write a Letter" data-description="Delivery start-ups are back. Here are five metrics that can help you determine if you have a customer-retention problem. And six ways to kill an employee&#039;s productivity.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Home Depot <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/20/business/daily-stock-market-activity.html?partner=socialflow&amp;smid=tw-nytimesbusiness">earnings and economic data</a> encourage the markets.</li>
<li>Homebuilding <a href="//news.yahoo.com/u-home-builder-sentiment-seven-month-high-august-140821072--sector.html">stocks rose</a>, boosted by data that showed homebuilder sentiment rose in August to its highest level since January.</li>
<li>The inflation rate takes <a href="//www.ibtimes.com/inflation-rate-takes-center-stage-week-economists-markets-eye-hint-next-fed-rate-move-1661804#.U">center stage this week</a> as economists and markets try to figure out the Federal Reserveâs next move.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Square is expanding its <a href="//bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/19/square-expands-its-cash-advance-service/">cash advance service</a>.</li>
<li>Here is why <a href="https://www.americanexpress.com/us/small-business/openforum/articles/why-crowdfunding-favors-women-owned-businesses/">crowdfunding favors</a> women-owned businesses.</li>
<li>Consumer loans <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/blog/2014/08/consumer-loans-jump-40-percent-at-st-louis-banks.html">jump 40 percent</a> at St. Louis banks.</li>
<li>Small-business lending is likely to be a <a href="//www.inc.com/jeremy-quittner/small-business-lending-recovers-slowly-and-small-loans-disappear.html">hot topic</a> at this weekâs economic summit in Jackson Hole.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-87922"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Ups</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/24/magazine/delivery-start-ups-are-back-like-its-1999.html">Delivery start-ups</a> &#8212; remember Kozmo and Webvan? &#8212; are back.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A co-founder and chief executive of a clothing retailer <a href="//www.inc.com/christine-lagorio/real-price-of-fast-growth-at-j-hilburn.html">decides to step down under pressure</a> despite the company&#8217;s very fast growth.</li>
<li>A dry cleaner offers tips for <a href="//www.greatfallstribune.com/story/money/2014/08/18/great-falls-business-owner-offers-construction-tips/14223527/">surviving construction</a> work in front of a business.</li>
<li>Here are five metrics that can help you determine if you have <a href="https://www.sweettoothrewards.com/blog/retention-problem-5-metrics-help-find-answer/">a customer-retention problem</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A <a href="//www.nydailynews.com/life-style/eats/stylish-n-10-year-old-started-cookie-company-article-1.1907595">stylish 10-year-old is the chief executive</a> of his own cookie company in New Jersey.</li>
<li>A British entrepreneur has found a way to <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/jasperhamill/2014/08/18/entrepreneur-hits-the-jackpot-by-handing-out-free-money/">make money by giving it away</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Some believe that big corporate layoffs could represent an <a href="//smallbusiness.foxbusiness.com/entrepreneurs/2014/08/18/big-corporate-layoffs-great-opportunity-for-small-businesses/">opportunity</a> for small businesses looking to hire.</li>
<li>Here are six <a href="//www.huffingtonpost.com/jill-keto/6-ways-to-kill-your-employees-productivity-_b_5682684.html">ways to kill</a> an employee&#8217;s productivity.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Facebook&#8217;sÂ <a href="//www.searchenginepeople.com/blog/125-start-to-success.html">Start to Success program</a> gives small businesses an opportunity to work with a Facebook account manager, but the businesses have to spend at least $50 a day on Facebook advertising.</li>
<li>Here are a few marketing and sales ideas <a href="//www.hartfordbusiness.com/ARTICLE/20140818/PRINTEDITION/308149941">that get businesses</a> in trouble.</li>
<li>Tory Burch had no experience, so she built her brand based on her own <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3034283/the-secret-to-tory-burchs-success-storytelling?partner=rss">story</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The wealthy and the poor <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/19/upshot/inequality-and-web-search-trends.html?ref=business&amp;abt=0002&amp;abg=1">search the Internet for very different things</a>.</li>
<li>An online <a href="https://blog.kissmetrics.com/online-customer-research-guide/?">expert shares</a> the websites, tools and techniques that have proven effective for him when researching a target market.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s why you <a href="//blog.brazencareerist.com/2014/08/18/stop-emailing-write-letter-instead/?">should stop</a> emailing &#8212; and write a letter instead.</li>
<li>Microsoftâs Azure service goes <a href="//www.pcworld.com/article/2466520/azure-services-down-again.html">down</a> again.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Facebook <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/Innovation/Horizons/2014/0818/Facebook-adds-satire-tag.-Can-you-tell-when-a-news-story-is-fake">adds</a> a âsatireâ tag to make it easier to spot fake news stories.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s what the Ferguson crisis can teach us about <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/08/19/how-facebook-and-twitter-control-what-you-see-about-ferguson/">how Twitter and Facebook handle content</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bourbon production has reached its <a href="//bigstory.ap.org/article/bourbon-production-reaches-high-point-70s?">highest point</a> since the 1970s.</li>
<li>The governors of Massachusetts and New Hampshire are <a href="//www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2014/08/18/massachusetts-new-hampshire-governors-step-in-to-help-negotiations-in/">trying to broker a deal</a> to end a monthlong standoff at a New England grocery store chain.</li>
<li>An Ohio business chamber <a href="//businessjournaldaily.com/awards-events/regional-chamber-cancels-young-2014-trade-show-2014-8-18">cancels</a> a trade show, attributing its decision to a lack of participation and &#8220;the changing nature of the shale industry here.&#8221;</li>
<li>Steve Ballmer <a href="//www.theverge.com/2014/8/18/6033963/steve-ballmer-is-very-excited-to-be-the-new-owner-of-the-la-clippers">is introduced</a> as the new owner of the Los Angeles Clippers.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s how America <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/08/18/how-america-fell-out-of-love-with-canned-tuna/">fell out of love with canned tuna</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World<br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/19/business/e-bike-sales-are-surging-in-europe.html">E-Bike sales are surging</a> in Europe.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Cash Flow</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s one way to <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/19/business/conference-crashers-make-contacts-but-dont-register.html">save money on conferences and trade shows</a>.</li>
<li><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/08/18/tax-burden-in-u-s-not-as-heavy-as-it-looks-study-finds/">Corporate taxes in the United States</a> may not be the heavy burden many claim.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Many businesses blame the Affordable Care Act for <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101927667">increasing</a> employee health coverage costs, according to two surveys by the Federal Reserve Bank of New York.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The wearable electronics market is expected <a href="//www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/wearable-electronics-market-to-hit-us8-billion-value-by-2018-271697581.html">to hit</a> $8 billion by 2018.</li>
<li>Wealthy car collectors <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101927168#_gus">spent more</a> than $400 million for collectible cars at an auction over the weekend. Is there a vintage car bubble?</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
